[
    {
        "content": "<p>Assume a goal can be solved both by <code>grind</code> and by one of the following tactics:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>aesop</code></li>\n<li><code>assumption</code></li>\n<li><code>congr</code></li>\n<li><code>contradiction</code></li>\n<li><code>decide</code></li>\n<li><code>norm_num</code></li>\n<li><code>omega</code></li>\n<li><code>rfl</code></li>\n<li><code>ring</code></li>\n<li><code>simp</code></li>\n<li><code>tauto</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>For which pairs of tactics (<code>grind</code>, one of the above) is <code>grind</code> likely going to be the better choice (once it has been released)?</p>",
        "id": 524600614,
        "sender_full_name": "Louis Cabarion",
        "timestamp": 1750196182
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>IIRC it's going to be strictly better than <code>omega</code>.</p>",
        "id": 524611233,
        "sender_full_name": "Marcus Rossel",
        "timestamp": 1750203552
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is <code>grind</code> suitable for / intended to be registered with <code>hint</code>? If so, I think that would make the decision about how best to use hint in the environment of other tactics much simpler.</p>",
        "id": 524611621,
        "sender_full_name": "Bolton Bailey",
        "timestamp": 1750203911
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Together with <code>grind</code> an extensible tactic called <code>try?</code> will be released which is like <code>hint</code> but also knows how to use multiple tactics in some cases. For example, this works on the latest nightly:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">doubleTheLengthPlusOne</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">::</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">xs</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">doubleTheLengthPlusOne</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">xs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">l</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">doubleTheLengthPlusOne</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">l</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">l</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">length</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- `try this: fun_induction doubleTheLengthPlusOne &lt;;&gt; grind`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">try?</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 524631461,
        "sender_full_name": "Markus Himmel",
        "timestamp": 1750223661
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Will <code>try?</code> solve everything that <code>hint</code> does? Does it use the same hint-tactic registry?</p>",
